&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a passionate, motivated leader ready to take on a new challenge in the field of children and young people’s nursing?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced children’s nurse to join our team as Ward Manager and lead in the delivery of high quality care for patients and their families , ensuring the ward team are well led and operationally efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 21 is a 25 bedded medical ward, caring for children and young people from 0- 18 years, with a wide range of conditions and a separate area for adolescents. It is part of a progressive department, with good development opportunities and a supportive and enthusiastic multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate will have previous clinical and managerial experience at Band 6 or above , be patient focused and an excellent role model, enabling others to learn and develop . If you feel you meet this description then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cathy Brammer (Lead Nurse for Children and Young People)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: cathy.brammer@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 854605&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
